snippet.textDisplay: Billie gave a great, truly commendable performance. Her composure in the presence of the entire film industry, at such a young age, is remarkable. Eventhough she has millions of fans, this was very high pressure and she pulled it off. HOWEVER, for such a personal and emotional concept (in memorium), I'd have expected them to have requested a singer with a more mature fanbase, who are representative of the film demographic. Otherwise, you have millions of fans watching for Billie only, which I feel reduces the respect for those who passed away. In my opinion, this was the wrong call, but all credit to Billie.
